# Memory Bank Context Requirements

This rule enforces the memory bank context requirements defined in @file .clinerules.

## Core Requirements

1. At the start of EVERY task:
   - ALL memory bank files MUST be read
   - This is not optional
   - Files must be read in the hierarchical order defined in the memory bank structure

2. Memory Bank Core Files (all required):
   - @file memory-bank/projectbrief.md
   - @file memory-bank/productContext.md
   - @file memory-bank/activeContext.md
   - @file memory-bank/systemPatterns.md
   - @file memory-bank/techContext.md
   - @file memory-bank/progress.md

## Documentation Updates

Updates to memory bank files are required when:
1. New project patterns are discovered
2. Significant changes are implemented
3. User explicitly requests with "update memory bank"
4. Context needs clarification

## Workflow Enforcement

The AI must:
1. Verify all memory bank files are read before proceeding with any task
2. Follow the Plan Mode or Act Mode workflow as defined in @file .clinerules
3. Maintain @file memory-bank/journal.md to capture project intelligence
4. Document all significant decisions and changes

## Validation

Before proceeding with any task, verify:
1. All required memory bank files have been read
2. Current context is fully understood
3. Any necessary updates to memory bank files are completed
4. Changes are documented appropriately

For detailed requirements and workflows, refer to @file .clinerules
